.cs 7 on
.item 'BROADCAST Command' 'Added on 07/08/82 by LSO'
.boxon
BROADCAST {port-id|front-end|ALL} [message]
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
Required Privileges:  OPERATOR

The BROADCAST command transmits a message either system wide or to a specific
community.  If there is no message specified, the message set by the SET
MESSAGE command would be transmitted.

.* SELECT 'BROADCAST Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION PORT-ID,N,TID,UUU,GG.UUU,'NAME'
.ix port-id 'on BROADCAST Command'
port-id\\\\\\\\\is the line address.  Type HELP PORT-ID for a description of
                port-id.

.* OPTION FRONT-END
.ix front-end 'on BROADCAST Command'
front-end\\\\\\\the name of a particular communications controller (e.g.,
                1270A).

.* OPTION ALL
.optix ALL
ALL\\\\\\\\\\\\\all ports connected to all the front ends.

.* OPTION MESSAGE
.ix message 'on BROADCAST Command'
message\\\\\\\\\is a single line message to be broadcasted to the users.
.cs 7 off
